// Synthetic exemplars (source=synthetic_v38) to address thin-tail
// intents in the librarian-labeled set. Targeted at specific gold-set
// failure modes; see findings/2026-05-13_v38_classifier.md.
//
// Style: mirrors real LibChat phrasing (conversational, sometimes
// short, occasionally typo'd). Each is a plausible user message --
// not a sentence a librarian would write, a sentence a user would.
//
// Rules for adding more:
//   1. One intent per row, source: "synthetic_v38" always.
//   2. No duplicate utterances across the whole exemplars set
//      (run scripts/pack_labeled_v38.py to validate; the packer
//      doesn't enforce dedupe but the diff report will surface
//      collisions).
//   3. Phrase like a user, not a librarian. "where is wertz" beats
//      "What is the location of the Wertz Art & Architecture Library?"
//   4. Cover the variants in the labeling guide's tie-break rules,
//      not just the central case.
//
// location_directions: building-level "where is X library" queries.
// The librarian-labeled set covers room/department locations well but
// has zero "where is the building itself" examples. Gold set
// expects location_directions for all 7 such queries and they all
// failed pre-synth.
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "Where is Wertz?", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "where is wertz library", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "What's the address of King Library?", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "address for king library", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "Where is Gardner-Harvey Library?", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
{"intent": "location_directions", "utterance": "How do I find Rentschler Library?", "source": "synthetic_v38"}
